<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Friend I am having the same problem.  I only put 5 points into strength.  Something should be done about the weight thing.  I can make my own arrows but they run out fast.  I have to buy arrows out in the field.  It is a bummer.  I usually carry 140 arrows.  That is almost my weight limit.  When I start getting loot and it weighs me down I drop arrows.  If I am lucky I will be in a group with a Clerk and they give me a nice strength buffs.  The weight limit is so tedious it has become a real hassle.  I don't mind spending money for arrows, but I don&#8217;t like having to leave a group to find arrows or make arrows.  I have had problems with groups becoming very impatient with me having to get more arrows.  I have been kicked out of some groups because of it.  I think it would be cool if maybe the better arrows would weigh a lot less so I could carry 300.  I would also like to be able to group arrows up to 100 not just 40 per slot in my bag.  Right now the scout class needs some teaking.  I am hoping poison arrows, and fire arrows will be implemented.  Then we could spend time and money learning a poison skill.  Scouts would really be able to kite if they had a poison arrow that worked like a dot.  I wonder if the melees could get pull off us then?  <BR>If the weight problem is not worked out I hope I can get some nice strength items.  That way I could carry more arrows.   So far everything for my class seems to be geared for quickness and dexterity.  If those are the main stream items available for the scout class it would be better for the base class to be a Britain.  The reason being they have more hit points more strength and if the majority of the items the scouts gets are geared toward dexterity and quickness then the items will help your character more over all.  I get the feeling that the development team is being very careful with the scout class.  It is important for the scout class not to be too powerful.  <BR>Maybe if we have to keep getting arrows the development team could give us some kind of running bonus?  Maybe make the arrows lighter?  Give scouts more strength?  Maybe the scouts could hire a NPC to follow them around carrying their arrows.<BR>For now I will have to deal with not getting invited into groups or to continue getting kicked out of groups because I am too high maintenance for certain types of players.  It has only happened two times that I am aware of so far.  It really isn&#8217;t unplayable it usually only takes thirty minutes to re-supply.  <BR>  <IMG SRC="eek.gif" border="0">
