<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Man, whats up with archery? Sure the dmg can be decent, but its a total pain in the ass.<P>I gotta open inven screen, equip bow, move icon to hot bar, select target, click once, wait 5 sec, click again, then when mob is in melee range I gotta open inven again and unequip bow(which also removes the icon from the hot bar, this really pisses me off), close inven and hit F-6.<P>My god, talk about a BS interface.<BR>If there was a way to keep the damn icon on the damn hot bar I'd be happy.<P>Whats the problem with having the icon stay up?<BR>Why not give us a hot key to equip/unequip bow, without going through the inven screen hassle? (BTW I can't stand having the screens up while I'm doing anything, the chat bar is enough of a vision restriction.)<BR>Why not have our bows automatically unequip when we hit F-6 for melee?<P>EQ has thier archers (rangers) light years ahead of DAoC. <BR>They've got quivers that not only can reduce arrow wieght, but also hasten your shot delay.<BR>When they hit melee attack the bow is automatically put away. <BR>You don't have to equip your bow or arrows every time you want to fire, they remain in their own ranged slots ready to be used at the press of a button.<BR>EQ has alot of problems as far as archery mechanics, but the EQ archery interface blows this garbage outa the water!
</FONT>
